<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RECONDITIONING BRAKE DRUMS AND SHOES - REPLACING LINING/BLOCKS - CHECKING LINING INSTALLATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CHECKING LINING INSTALLATION</title>
        <para>After the lining is installed, check tightness of lining to shoe, with a feeler gauge along the arc of
            shoe and lining/web, and between the shoe and lining/web at the ends of the lining or web (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0400729">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0400729" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0400729" filename="../figg04/g0400729.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 29. Check Lining Installation</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>A gap of 0.010 inch (0.25 mm) maximum is acceptable between the shoe and lining along the sides and ends
            of the assembly, except between the double web. Between the shoe and webs a 0.025 inch (0.64 mm) gap is
            acceptable (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0400730">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0400730" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0400730" filename="../figg04/g0400730.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Acceptable Gap Between Shoe and Lining</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
